250 grams Mozzarella
2 unit(s) Tomato
40 grams Salad Leaves
80 grams Sliced Irish Ham
30 grams Green Pesto
2 sachet(s) Balsamic Glaze
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Oil

Thinly slice the tomato.
Tear the ham into pieces.

Just before serving toss the salad leaves with a drizzle of oil and half the balsamic glaze.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Divide the tomato slices between plates.
Place a handful of dressed salad leaves in the middle of each plate and place a whole ball of mozzarella on top of the salad.
Drizzle over the pesto and remaining balsamic glaze.
Crack some pepper on top.